Sentencas: The oxidation behavior and electrical property of a newly designed Fe-Cr alloy with addition of 1.05 wt.% Mn, 0.52 wt.% Ti, 2.09 wt.% Mo and other elements, such as La, Y and Zr have been investigated isothermally or cyclically at 750 degrees C in air for up to 1000 h. With a coefficient of thermal expansion matched to SOFC cell the alloy demonstrates excellent oxidation resistance and low area specific resistance of the components oxide scale.
Titulo: Development of a Fe-Cr alloy for interconnect application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermally grown oxide scale presents a multi-layered structure with conductive Mn-Cr spinel in-between the underneath Cr2O3 and the top Mn2O3.
Titulo: Development of a Fe-Cr alloy for interconnect application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxidation rate constants obtained under both isothermal and cyclic oxidation condition are in the range of 5.1 x 10(-14) to 7.6 x 10(-14) g(2) cm(-4) s(-1), and the measured area specific resistance at 750 degrees C after 1000 h oxidation is around 10 m Omega cm(2), lower than that of the conventional Fe-Cr stainless steels and comparable with that of the Ni-based alloys.
Titulo: Development of a Fe-Cr alloy for interconnect application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal cycling seems to improve the oxide scale adherence and promotes the formation of the highly conductive Mn2O3, and in turn, to enhance the oxidation resistance and electrical property.
Titulo: Development of a Fe-Cr alloy for interconnect application in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
